<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="1" id="b4b2da4c-d89c-5571-b9ce-bcc927a3a8c6" activityNameId="020fd8b0-01d7-48cd-b9c4-b95ee0a6378f" parentActivityId="4f624ca6-2ddf-41dc-81f8-c6c43eda6335" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">market for adhesive mortar</activityName>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce 'adhesive mortar',  within the geography of Global.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">This activity ends with the supply of 'adhesive mortar',  to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">This is the market for  'adhesive mortar', in the Global geography.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">The product "adhesive mortar" is produced with a main material of mortar. A user employing this module should add 0.048 kg water per kg dry product (not included here). It is used in buildings and infrastructure as a sealant. Adhesive mortar is used for laying of tiles, plates, small mosaics, light-weight and high resistance foam slab for indoor and outdoor use. It glues to concrete, plaster, floor pavement, anhydrite floor, masonry, gypsum plaster board, lightweight and autoclaved aerated concrete.</text>
        </generalComment>
        <tag>ConvertedDataset</tag>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="415b558b-318c-427e-9a3c-24a687363c14">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">EcoSpold01Categories</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">mortar and plaster/production</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <classification classificationId="36cd730c-4485-4fe9-8efe-8850f771796d">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">2394:Manufacture of cement, lime and plaster</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="34dbbff8-88ce-11de-ad60-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">GLO</shortname>
      </geography>
